urn to Islam means the recovery of traditions destroyed under Communism.Islam after Communism reasons that the fear of a rampant radical Islam that dominates both Western thought and many of Central Asia’s governments should be tempered with an understanding of the politics of antiterrorism, which allows governments to justify their own authoritarian policies by casting all opposition as extremist. Placing the Central Asian experience in the broad comparative perspective of the history of modern Islam, Khalid argues against essentialist views of Islam and Muslims and provides a nuanced and well-informed discussion of the forces at work in this crucial region.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aIslam and politicszAsia, Central. 0aIslamzAsia, Central. 0aIslamic renewalzAsia, Central. 0aReligion and politicszAsia, Central. 70(DE-601)1041624300(DE-588)4041282-9aNationalbewusstsein2gnd 70(DE-601)1057512430(DE-588)4123963-5aPolitisches Programm2gnd 70(DE-601)1061780080(DE-588)4051238-1aSäkularisierung2gnd 70(DE-601)1061871040(DE-588)4049416-0aReligionspolitik2gnd 70(DE-601)1062834990(DE-588)4027743-4aIslam2gnd 7aRELIGION / Islam / General.2bisacsh  aantiterrorism.  aauthoritarianism.  abolshevik project.  acentral asia.  acommunism.  adiplomacy.  aethnographic identities.  aextremist.  agod and religion.  ahistory of the soviet union.  ahistory.  aislam.  aislamic learning.  amodern islam.  amuslims in russia.  amuslims in the soviet union.  amuslims.  apolitics.  aradical islam.  areligion and politics.  areligion.  areligious persecution.  areligious tradition.  areligious.  arussia.  arussian history.  arussian muslims.  asoviet assault on islam.  asoviet union.  aterrorism.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniver